page.title: 13RUGBY STATION
page.content: In 1885 Rugby Station was built. In 1985 the station is important. The{ {Advanced Passenger Train}known as{ {A.P.T}travels through Rugby and is the fastest and newest train in 1985.The{ {Class 9 engineering freight}is the slowest train in 1985.The {Lion}and {Queens Train}are the oldest trains to pass through Rugby.The Rugby Station has 200 trains passing each day.Most of them are {express passenger}trains. The pay bill clarke books trains on and off and he makes sure the wages are alright.Most people thought that working at the station was an enjoyable but busy job. The station seemed quite large and busy . They seemed very friendly there, and most of them were busy. { }
